FT  24 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Amber Pounds 1.9m at midway
Amber Industrial Holdings, the specialist chemicals maker and distributor,
turned in pre-tax profits of Pounds 1.87m for the six months to September
30. This compared with Pounds 2.43m last time, but which included Pounds
724,000 on the disposal of operations.
Turnover rose by 5.4 per cent to Pounds 11.8m (Pounds 11.2m).
Earnings per share, came to 26.2p, against 42.5p or 24p adjusted to exclude
the disposal. The interim dividend has been stepped up to 7p (6p).
The company is 75 per cent owned by Caledonia Investments.
